Everything in candidates/ is licensed under MIT, unless an individual
candidate subdirectory ships its own LICENSE file overriding this.

Candidates are independent implementations of the emulator ABI defined
in spec/ABI.md. They do not link GPL code statically — they are compiled
to standalone WebAssembly modules and communicate with the grader
across a module boundary.

